161
00:07:45,365 --> 00:07:46,633
I ran to the seaside platform,
and you came to find me.

162
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:47,634
We made some random wishes together.

163
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:48,768
Did you forget?

164
00:07:48,768 --> 00:07:50,037
What are you talking about?

165
00:07:50,037 --> 00:07:52,472
I've never had a roadside banquet with you.

166
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:56,709
Li Wan Zhe.

167
00:07:56,709 --> 00:07:58,611
What's my name?

168
00:07:58,611 --> 00:07:59,646
Zhong Xiao You.

169
00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:00,914
What do you mean, Zhong Xiao You?

170
00:08:00,914 --> 00:08:02,315
I'm He Xiang Yong.

171
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:03,716
He Xiang Yong?

172
00:08:03,716 --> 00:08:05,317
Who's that?

173
00:08:06,052 --> 00:08:07,353
Listen to me.

174
00:08:07,353 --> 00:08:08,688
I don't know how you found out,

175
00:08:08,688 --> 00:08:11,291
but I hope you don't go around telling people.

176
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:12,291
Li Wan Zhe!

177
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,292
Li Wan Zhe, you...

178
00:08:13,292 --> 00:08:14,994
Li Wan Zhe!

179
00:08:17,797 --> 00:08:19,999
I'm doomed.

180
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:21,835
What exactly went wrong?

181
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:23,802
How could this happen?

182
00:08:35,215 --> 00:08:37,650
You're back.

183
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:39,685
Are you okay?

184
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:46,192
Someone named Xi Xi called looking for you.

185
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,227
She said she's your friend.

186
00:08:49,896 --> 00:08:51,630
What did she say?

187
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:55,301
She asked for He Xiang Yong at first,

188
00:08:55,301 --> 00:08:57,670
but then she asked for you.

189
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,705
She left her number.

190
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:06,445
So, who is He Xiang Yong?

191
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:36,309
Hello, Xi Xi.

192
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:38,377
Do you still remember me?

193
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:41,781
Even if you're not the editor I remember,

194
00:09:41,781 --> 00:09:43,383
you're the only one I could think of.

195
00:09:43,383 --> 00:09:45,451
<i>He Xiang Yong.</i>

196
00:09:48,454 --> 00:09:51,157
Thank goodness.

197
00:09:51,157 --> 00:09:53,359
Xi Xi, listen to me.

198
00:09:53,359 --> 00:09:55,762
Last night, I was clearly with Chen Hao Wei
at a hotel on the main island.

199
00:09:55,762 --> 00:09:58,097
But when I woke up today,
I was back on Starry Islet.

200
00:09:58,097 --> 00:09:59,165
And when I asked Chen Hao Wei,

201
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:01,034
he told me he didn't know
who He Xiang Yong was.

202
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:03,036
But he clearly recognized me last night!

203
00:10:03,036 --> 00:10:04,036
Then I went to ask my dad.

204
00:10:04,036 --> 00:10:05,905
But he told me he'd never been married.

205
00:10:05,905 --> 00:10:08,241
And the things in my house...
my photos, my mom's photos,

206
00:10:08,241 --> 00:10:09,876
our family portrait, they've all disappeared.

207
00:10:09,876 --> 00:10:11,010
Then I went to find Li Wan Zhe,

208
00:10:11,010 --> 00:10:12,545
but he said he didn't recognize me either.

209
00:10:12,545 --> 00:10:14,681
But before this, he was clearly the only one

210
00:10:14,681 --> 00:10:15,782
- who always remembered me.
<i>- Calm down.</i>

211
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,217
<i>Listen to me.</i>

212
00:10:18,217 --> 00:10:20,286
I dreamed that I went to Starry Islet.

213
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,121
Outside the grocery store, I met someone

214
00:10:22,121 --> 00:10:25,391
who knew I liked bitter melon black tea.

215
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:27,594
The grocery store?

216
00:10:27,594 --> 00:10:29,796
Was it Hong?

217
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:31,864
He said that when a wish comes true,

218
00:10:31,864 --> 00:10:34,834
it also means you'll lose something.

219
00:10:34,834 --> 00:10:38,438
I think the wish is backfiring.

220
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:41,440
<i>Time and space are becoming distorted.</i>

221
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:48,981
The card I drew also confirms what Hong said.

222
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,452
So, if I get Zhong Xiao You's identity,

223
00:10:52,452 --> 00:10:54,954
is He Xiang Yong destined to vanish?

224
00:10:54,954 --> 00:10:56,389
Is everything I got from that wish

225
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:58,291
going to be this short-lived?

226
00:10:58,291 --> 00:10:59,292
<i>Xi Xi, what should I do?</i>

227
00:10:59,292 --> 00:11:01,027
I finally made up with my dad.

228
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:02,929
I finally got a second chance
with Chen Hao Wei.

229
00:11:02,929 --> 00:11:04,797
What can I do to save all of this?

230
00:11:04,797 --> 00:11:06,065
Is there anything I can do

231
00:11:06,065 --> 00:11:07,066
to make things go back to normal?

232
00:11:07,066 --> 00:11:08,134
Xi Xi, please help me.

233
00:11:08,134 --> 00:11:09,636
<i>He Xiang Yong.</i>

234
00:11:09,636 --> 00:11:13,405
If you give up now, the game is over.

235
00:11:16,109 --> 00:11:18,645
Go find Hong first.

236
00:11:18,645 --> 00:11:20,246
Why look for Hong?

237
00:11:20,246 --> 00:11:22,015
I don't think he's an ordinary person.

238
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,316
He might be the only one who can help.

239
00:11:38,765 --> 00:11:41,634
Hong!

240
00:11:41,634 --> 00:11:44,002
Hong!

241
00:11:56,383 --> 00:11:57,383
Mr. De.

242
00:11:57,383 --> 00:11:59,285
Have you seen Hong?

243
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:00,586
Isn't he sitting outside?

244
00:12:00,586 --> 00:12:02,988
- No.
- He's not?

245
00:12:27,061 --> 00:12:30,414
[Ask Star AI...]
[When'll wishes upon shooting stars backfire?]

246
00:12:30,414 --> 00:12:32,222
[Please wait...]

247
00:12:32,222 --> 00:12:33,525
[Sorry, the system doesn't have an answer.]

248
00:12:37,990 --> 00:12:40,727
Even AI can't solve this.

249
00:12:40,727 --> 00:12:43,061
What am I supposed to do?

250
00:12:45,665 --> 00:12:47,567
Li Wan Zhe, the sweet soup is ready.

251
00:12:47,567 --> 00:12:49,001
Bring it down for me.

252
00:12:49,001 --> 00:12:50,336
Li Wan Zhe!

253
00:12:50,336 --> 00:12:51,904
What on earth are you busy with?

254
00:12:51,904 --> 00:12:53,406
Get your butt down here and work!

255
00:12:53,406 --> 00:12:54,674
You put on the same act every day.

256
00:12:54,674 --> 00:12:56,275
Aren't you tired of it?

257
00:12:56,275 --> 00:12:57,443
Tao!

258
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:58,845
Coming!

259
00:12:58,845 --> 00:12:59,979
Chief, you're here, too.

260
00:12:59,979 --> 00:13:01,313
Okay.

261
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:06,886
I'll give you fewer tapioca balls

262
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:08,121
and more mung beans, okay?

263
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,288
- Sure.
- All right.

264
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:11,390
Zhe Ma, have you seen Hong?

265
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:13,193
Hong? Why are you looking for Hong?

266
00:13:13,193 --> 00:13:14,193
Doesn't Hong live by the temple?

267
00:13:14,193 --> 00:13:15,495
I have something very important to ask him.

268
00:13:15,495 --> 00:13:16,763
He lives behind the temple.

269
00:13:16,763 --> 00:13:18,831
No, he lives in the sixth house
from the end of Coastal Road.

270
00:13:18,831 --> 00:13:19,899
But I remember him being at the grocery store.

271
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:22,335
What are you talking about?
He lives right by the pier.

272
00:13:22,335 --> 00:13:23,536
He lives behind the temple.

273
00:13:23,536 --> 00:13:25,638
He used to lay out his straw mat there.

274
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:27,774
He even did his laundry there.

275
00:13:27,774 --> 00:13:28,808
Li Wan Zhe.

276
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,976
What do you want?

277
00:13:31,878 --> 00:13:33,913
I know you don't believe me right now,

278
00:13:33,913 --> 00:13:35,648
but I still have to tell you.

279
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:37,784
If we want to solve this problem,

280
00:13:37,784 --> 00:13:39,819
Hong seems to be the key.

281
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,154
Are we even that close?

282
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,289
And how do you know so much about me?

283
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:45,758
I'm warning you, don't tell anyone.

284
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:48,260
I didn't tell anyone.

285
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:52,365
- Xiao You.
- Hao Wei, want some shaved ice?

286
00:13:52,365 --> 00:13:53,866
Later. I'll eat later.

287
00:13:53,866 --> 00:13:54,834
- Okay.
- Xiao You.

288
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:55,835
Come back with me now.

289
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,970
Mr. He is already angry.

290
00:13:57,970 --> 00:13:59,972
Here, catch.

291
00:13:59,972 --> 00:14:01,674
Skipping work, huh?

292
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:03,342
Go home.

293
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:06,612
What?

294
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:08,814
How did he disappear just from making a call?

295
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:11,450
I'm leaving now.

296
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:13,219
- Bye.
- Ride safely.

297
00:14:13,219 --> 00:14:14,420
Okay.

298
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:16,388
Weirdo.

299
00:14:32,004 --> 00:14:34,906
What was it you wanted to tell me?

300
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:49,455
In the two months you've been here,

301
00:14:49,455 --> 00:14:51,823
it's the first time I've seen you so flustered.

302
00:15:01,067 --> 00:15:02,635
All right.

303
00:15:02,635 --> 00:15:05,170
It's okay if you don't want to say it now.

304
00:15:18,017 --> 00:15:20,686
When you're ready to talk, just let me know.

305
00:15:25,491 --> 00:15:28,661
I'll call Mr. He and say we'll be back late.

306
00:15:28,661 --> 00:15:31,096
Where do you want to go?

307
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:39,138
Come on.

308
00:15:39,138 --> 00:15:40,506
Let's get a little mushy.

309
00:15:40,506 --> 00:15:41,941
Come on.

310
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,875
Get closer.

311
00:16:03,162 --> 00:16:05,665
So, you finally decided to come back.

312
00:16:05,665 --> 00:16:07,700
Looking for Hong...

313
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:10,369
Everyone on Starry Islet knows about it.

314
00:16:10,369 --> 00:16:13,405
Well? Did you find him?

315
00:16:20,846 --> 00:16:23,148
What is wrong with you?

316
00:16:23,783 --> 00:16:24,884
No matter what's going on,

317
00:16:24,884 --> 00:16:27,219
you can't just run off without a word.

318
00:16:27,219 --> 00:16:29,655
Who's going to do the work at the inn?

319
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,023
Hao Wei or me?

320
00:16:31,023 --> 00:16:32,191
Mr. He.

321
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:33,926
Xiao You was looking for Hong...

322
00:16:33,926 --> 00:16:36,828
- It must be because...
- He has a mouth, he can speak for himself.

323
00:16:38,898 --> 00:16:40,766
You're acting very strange today.

324
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:43,401
You won't even offer an explanation.

325
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:46,339
I'm sorry.

326
00:16:46,339 --> 00:16:49,108
It's my own problem, I'll find a way to fix it.

327
00:16:49,108 --> 00:16:52,711
I won't let it affect the inn work again.

328
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:00,386
Forget it.

329
00:17:00,386 --> 00:17:03,688
You young people have your own ideas.

330
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:10,629
But if you really run into
something you can't solve,

331
00:17:10,629 --> 00:17:11,764
even if you don't want to tell me,

332
00:17:11,764 --> 00:17:15,501
you can go to Mr. Hua, or go see Angela.

333
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:16,736
We're your elders, after all.

334
00:17:16,736 --> 00:17:19,237
You can at least talk to us.

335
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:26,912
Xiao You.

336
00:17:26,912 --> 00:17:29,282
You've had a long day. You must be hungry.

337
00:17:29,282 --> 00:17:30,282
I'll go make you something to eat.

338
00:17:30,282 --> 00:17:31,883
Wait here a moment.

339
00:17:32,785 --> 00:17:35,053
Let's eat. I'm starving.

340
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:47,054
Let's eat.

341
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:50,926
Thank you, Mr. He.

342
00:18:25,071 --> 00:18:27,939
What's wrong? Does it taste bad?

343
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:35,213
My parents also love
garlic shrimp rice noodles.

344
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,990
If you miss home, just go back.

345
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,259
You don't even need to ask for leave.

346
00:18:53,466 --> 00:18:55,234
Go on, get some rest.

347
00:18:55,234 --> 00:18:57,302
Over here.

348
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:03,208
Are you okay?

349
00:19:31,570 --> 00:19:32,771
Si Si.

350
00:19:32,771 --> 00:19:35,708
I'm here to pick up the batch
of brown sugar my mom ordered.

351
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,643
Wait a second. My dad's in the shower.

352
00:19:37,643 --> 00:19:38,978
Okay, thanks.

353
00:19:38,978 --> 00:19:40,746
Old man!

354
00:19:40,746 --> 00:19:42,431
It's Wan Zhe.

355
00:19:56,462 --> 00:19:58,697
Hong.

356
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,833
Do you know anything about
wishing upon a shooting star?

357
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,434
Why does Zhong Xiao You
keep saying that you're...

358
00:20:02,434 --> 00:20:03,769
that you're the key?

359
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:04,803
What do you mean I'm the key?

360
00:20:04,803 --> 00:20:06,071
I didn't make a wish.

361
00:20:06,071 --> 00:20:07,473
You did, didn't you?

362
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:08,774
I did.

363
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:10,242
Then what did you wish for?

364
00:20:10,242 --> 00:20:11,577
I didn't make a wish.

365
00:20:11,577 --> 00:20:12,945
I definitely didn't make a wish.

366
00:20:12,945 --> 00:20:15,748
It's all a secret.

367
00:20:15,748 --> 00:20:17,649
A secret?

368
00:20:18,317 --> 00:20:20,452
What do you mean?

369
00:20:21,520 --> 00:20:23,455
In this world,

370
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:26,425
no wall is completely soundproof.

371
00:20:26,425 --> 00:20:29,361
One day, the sea will bring you

372
00:20:29,361 --> 00:20:31,821
the message it wants to tell you.

373
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:34,633
It's right here.

374
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:37,002
What sea?

375
00:20:37,002 --> 00:20:39,338
Love like fireworks is burning up!

376
00:20:39,338 --> 00:20:41,941
Just like a fire!

377
00:20:41,941 --> 00:20:44,310
What fire? What's burning up?

378
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,579
Hong, what are you trying to say?

379
00:20:46,579 --> 00:20:49,214
I wanted to ask you about Zhong Xiao You.

380
00:20:51,617 --> 00:20:53,652
Here.

381
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:56,088
This is for you.

382
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,856
Don't come looking for me again.

383
00:20:57,856 --> 00:20:59,225
I'm going home.

384
00:20:59,225 --> 00:21:00,993
I'm going back to my home in the sea.

385
00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:02,294
I can finally go home.

386
00:21:02,294 --> 00:21:04,129
Wan Zhe.

387
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:09,935
My dad said to go get it yourself.

388
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:12,404
Can you even see with those sunglasses on?

389
00:21:12,404 --> 00:21:14,806
You don't get it, I'm a rocker.

390
00:21:24,683 --> 00:21:25,683
It's raining now.

391
00:21:25,683 --> 00:21:27,819
Why don't you go inside?

392
00:21:29,488 --> 00:21:32,090
I want to sit here a bit longer.

393
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:54,212
Go home if you want to.

394
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:57,149
Don't worry about the work here.

395
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:59,117
I'll handle it.

396
00:21:59,918 --> 00:22:02,687
This is my home.

397
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:06,925
You don't believe me, do you?

398
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:14,265
I knew you wouldn't believe me.

399
00:22:18,203 --> 00:22:20,405
Have you ever heard of déjà vu?

400
00:22:29,648 --> 00:22:32,251
Déjà vu is a sense of familiarity.

401
00:22:32,251 --> 00:22:35,220
It's a feeling that you've seen this before.

402
00:22:36,255 --> 00:22:39,757
Lately, when I talk to you,
I often get déjà vu.

403
00:22:46,131 --> 00:22:48,867
Actually, I'm curious about something.

404
00:22:50,903 --> 00:22:54,405
You said He Xiang Yong and I
were high school classmates.

405
00:22:55,441 --> 00:22:57,142
And you said you are He Xiang Yong.

406
00:22:57,142 --> 00:22:59,078
So...

407
00:22:59,078 --> 00:23:02,080
did anything happen between us before?

408
00:23:10,055 --> 00:23:12,391
In your senior year,

409
00:23:12,391 --> 00:23:14,692
you lost a basketball game.

410
00:23:16,028 --> 00:23:18,897
I pulled your hat down over your eyes,

411
00:23:19,498 --> 00:23:22,367
because I didn't want people to see you sad.

412
00:23:26,672 --> 00:23:30,008
In my senior year, I was studying for exams.

413
00:23:30,008 --> 00:23:32,510
I didn't play in any basketball games.

414
00:23:35,314 --> 00:23:37,116
On your 18th birthday,

415
00:23:37,116 --> 00:23:40,285
I drew a picture of a sea turtle for you

416
00:23:40,285 --> 00:23:43,222
as a birthday present.

417
00:23:43,222 --> 00:23:46,358
But I never received a sea turtle drawing.

418
00:23:46,358 --> 00:23:48,560
Then do you remember

419
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:51,262
how you used to love telling bad jokes?

420
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:14,352
The necklace around your neck...

421
00:24:15,521 --> 00:24:17,755
I gave that to you, too.

422
00:24:19,691 --> 00:24:21,826
This necklace?

423
00:24:22,694 --> 00:24:25,763
I bought this for myself
when I was on the main island.

424
00:24:28,967 --> 00:24:31,103
Forget it.

425
00:24:31,103 --> 00:24:33,806
There's no point in talking about it.

426
00:24:33,806 --> 00:24:36,442
You don't remember anyway.

427
00:24:36,442 --> 00:24:39,043
The more I say, the more disappointed I get.

428
00:24:44,216 --> 00:24:46,618
I think it's very interesting.

429
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:50,556
And you can draw?

430
00:24:50,556 --> 00:24:53,191
I've always admired people who can draw.

431
00:24:57,463 --> 00:24:58,997
<i>I want to follow your art.</i>

432
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:00,999
<i>Always, always, always...</i>

433
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:03,134
<i>I'll always be your number one fan.</i>

434
00:25:05,537 --> 00:25:08,640
Actually, what you just told me...

435
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,875
I think I have some memory of it.

436
00:25:13,479 --> 00:25:15,813
Didn't you say you didn't remember?

437
00:25:17,683 --> 00:25:19,884
It's just déjà vu.

438
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:24,323
The person in my dream is blurry.

439
00:25:24,323 --> 00:25:26,524
I can't see his face clearly.

440
00:25:27,759 --> 00:25:29,761
Then...

441
00:25:29,761 --> 00:25:31,996
what else did you dream about?

442
00:25:37,069 --> 00:25:38,103
If you ask me to think about it now,

443
00:25:38,103 --> 00:25:40,071
I won't be able to remember.

444
00:25:45,978 --> 00:25:49,280
This must be the consequence
of wishing upon a shooting star.

445
00:25:51,116 --> 00:25:54,152
Everyone will forget about me.

446
00:25:54,152 --> 00:25:57,956
Forget everything about He Xiang Yong.

447
00:25:57,956 --> 00:26:00,992
Shooting stars? Making a wish?

448
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:06,465
I know it's hard to believe.

449
00:26:06,465 --> 00:26:09,367
But it really happened to me.

450
00:26:11,537 --> 00:26:14,019
I've said those exact words to you before.

451
00:26:39,298 --> 00:26:41,165
Do you mind?

452
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:57,516
I kind of believe it now.

453
00:27:36,722 --> 00:27:38,568
- Want a drink?
- No thanks.

454
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:48,046
No.

455
00:27:48,934 --> 00:27:50,599
I wasn't asking you.

456
00:28:00,912 --> 00:28:02,914
So noisy.

457
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:05,750
It's late. Your mom will scold you again.

458
00:28:08,987 --> 00:28:11,657
Can you really not remember anything?

459
00:28:11,657 --> 00:28:13,191
Remember what?

460
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:14,426
Those two dishes.

461
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:16,627
Chicken feet and stinky tofu.

462
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:24,903
You used to pester me all the time.

463
00:28:24,903 --> 00:28:26,505
You kept following me around.

464
00:28:26,505 --> 00:28:28,507
And now...

465
00:28:28,507 --> 00:28:31,209
Anyway, I don't know how to explain it.

466
00:28:34,646 --> 00:28:36,515
Stop playing.

467
00:28:36,515 --> 00:28:37,616
Go home.

468
00:28:37,616 --> 00:28:39,051
I'm almost at the next level!

469
00:28:39,051 --> 00:28:41,553
Whatever.

470
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:42,988
Fine.

471
00:28:42,988 --> 00:28:46,057
Don't text me later to nag me.

472
00:28:47,826 --> 00:28:50,228
- See ya.
- Hey.

473
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:52,463
Are you really not staying?

474
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:56,201
Do you really want me to stay?

475
00:28:56,201 --> 00:28:57,982
Get lost!

476
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:00,995
Bye.

477
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:27,932
Damn, he really left.

478
00:30:34,032 --> 00:30:38,135
<i>Those moments of déjà vu you mentioned...</i>

479
00:30:38,737 --> 00:30:40,772
<i>One day,</i>

480
00:30:40,772 --> 00:30:43,274
<i>will you remember them?</i>

481
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:46,745
<i>Or...</i>

482
00:30:46,745 --> 00:30:49,714
<i>have I really been forgotten by everyone?</i>

483
00:30:52,957 --> 00:31:00,796
[Epilogue]

484
00:31:02,705 --> 00:31:08,519
[For you]

485
00:31:38,496 --> 00:31:40,532
Hong.

486
00:31:40,532 --> 00:31:42,433
What are you doing?

487
00:31:43,168 --> 00:31:45,537
I'm...

488
00:31:45,537 --> 00:31:46,771
watching the shooting stars.

489
00:31:46,771 --> 00:31:49,107
Watching shooting stars?

490
00:31:49,107 --> 00:31:51,743
But it's daytime.

491
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,311
I know there are shooting stars in the day.

492
00:31:53,311 --> 00:31:56,915
But... you shouldn't be able to see them.

493
00:31:56,915 --> 00:31:58,250
Dummy.

494
00:31:58,250 --> 00:32:00,285
That's because you aren't
looking with your heart.

495
00:32:00,285 --> 00:32:02,053
You have to look with your heart.

496
00:32:02,053 --> 00:32:04,121
With my heart?

497
00:32:04,789 --> 00:32:06,258
What do you mean?

498
00:32:06,258 --> 00:32:09,127
Do you want to make a wish on a shooting star?

499
00:32:09,127 --> 00:32:10,495
Please.

500
00:32:10,495 --> 00:32:13,398
I've heard that story since I was a kid.

501
00:32:13,398 --> 00:32:16,568
Has anyone's wish ever actually come true?

502
00:32:16,568 --> 00:32:18,803
Oh, that's because you're all
using the wrong method.

503
00:32:18,803 --> 00:32:20,569
The wrong method?

504
00:32:21,806 --> 00:32:22,807
Listen carefully.

505
00:32:22,807 --> 00:32:23,808
I'm only saying this once.

506
00:32:23,808 --> 00:32:25,643
Okay.

507
00:32:26,845 --> 00:32:28,980
This is a meteorite fragment.

508
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:30,615
A meteorite fragment?

509
00:32:30,615 --> 00:32:32,083
You have to...

510
00:32:32,083 --> 00:32:34,920
When the shooting star comes,
take this meteorite fragment...

511
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:36,921
and throw it into the sea.

512
00:32:38,690 --> 00:32:42,694
When this energy and your wish...
combine together...

513
00:32:42,694 --> 00:32:44,562
your wish will come true!

514
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:47,031
Are you serious?

515
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,034
Want to give it a try?

516
00:32:49,034 --> 00:32:51,002
Maybe next time. Next time.

517
00:32:51,002 --> 00:32:53,705
I have to go back and help at the shop.

518
00:32:53,705 --> 00:32:55,073
The tide is coming in soon.

519
00:32:55,073 --> 00:32:57,375
Do you want to head back together?

520
00:32:57,375 --> 00:32:59,144
Don't worry about me. Just go back.

521
00:32:59,144 --> 00:33:00,578
- Go on.
- All right then.

522
00:33:00,578 --> 00:33:02,380
- Take care of yourself.
- Okay, I will.

523
00:33:02,380 --> 00:33:04,682
- Bye-bye.
- Okay, bye.

524
00:33:52,998 --> 00:33:54,466
Are you here to check in?

525
00:33:54,466 --> 00:33:55,633
Chen Hao Wei.

526
00:33:55,633 --> 00:33:58,370
Sir? Are you checking in?

527
00:33:58,370 --> 00:34:00,038
I like you.

528
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:02,773
I like you.

529
00:34:04,009 --> 00:34:05,844
Have you ever heard of cellular memory

530
00:34:05,844 --> 00:34:07,412
or muscle memory?

531
00:34:07,412 --> 00:34:11,049
Your brain might forget,
but your heart never does.

532
00:34:11,049 --> 00:34:12,982
You remember, don't you?

